item.description: The Soviet flag is partly rooted in the French Revolution. Both sentiments were echoed in the Russian Revolution, and according to author Paul Spicker, the French Revolution's pursuits of liberty, quality, and fraternity "heavily influenced" Marxism. Red flags took on an explicitly socialist meaning in 1871 when the Paris Commune adopted the Red Banner as an emblem of socialist movements throughout Europe.
